---
// defense-in-depth-rings — Chapter 080 Lesson 3, "Walking the six error seams".
//
// Seam #3's senior insight: two checks guard a protected page, and only one of
// them authorizes. The proxy at the perimeter is a cheap presence gate; the
// in-component requireOrgUser() is the real authorization check.
//
// Layout — two NESTED boxes (concentric "rings"), so containment is spatial:
//   ┌─ proxy.ts (outer ring) ─────────────────────────────┐
//   │   "what slips past the outer ring" annotations      │
//   │   ┌─ requireOrgUser() (inner ring) ─────────────┐   │
//   │   │   the protected page body                   │   │
//   │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
//   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
// The annotations sit in the gap between the rings — exactly where the cases
// they describe live: past the outer gate, caught by the inner one.
//
// Palette pinned to this lesson's SixSeamsOverview figure: AMBER marks the outer
// ring as "checks presence, does NOT authorize" (the weaker guarantee), GREEN
// marks the inner ring as the real authorization gate. margin:0 resets defeat
// Starlight's injected prose margins; `not-content` opts the body out of prose
// styling.

import Figure from '../../../figures/Figure.astro';

const sans = "system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif";
const mono = 'ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace';

const GREEN = '#16a34a'; // the inner ring — real authorization
const AMBER = '#d97706'; // the outer ring — presence only, NOT authorization

const slips = [
	'membership revoked while the page sat open',
	'active org switched in another tab',
	'session expired in the gap between proxy and render',
];

const ALT =
	'Two nested boxes. The outer box is proxy.ts, the edge middleware: it checks the session cookie is present and bounces signed-out users to /sign-in, but does NOT authorize. Inside the outer box, before the inner box, sit three cases that slip past the outer ring: membership revoked while the page sat open, the active org switched in another tab, and the session expired in the gap between proxy and render. The inner box is requireOrgUser(), running inside the Server Component: it re-checks against the database and throws on no session or no active org, caught by error.tsx. Innermost is the protected page body, which renders only after the inner ring passes. Only the inner ring authorizes.';
---

<Figure caption="Two rings; only the inner one authorizes.">
	<div class="ddr not-content" role="img" aria-label={ALT}>
		<div class="ddr-outer">
			<span class="ddr-legend ddr-legend-outer">
				<span class="ddr-ring-num ddr-ring-num-outer">outer ring</span>
				<code class="ddr-file">proxy.ts</code>
			</span>

			<p class="ddr-role ddr-role-outer">
				Checks the session cookie is present, bounces signed-out users to{' '}
				<code class="ddr-inline">/sign-in</code>.
				<strong class="ddr-not">Does NOT authorize.</strong>
			</p>

			<div class="ddr-gap">
				<p class="ddr-gap-head">Slips past the outer ring →</p>
				<ul class="ddr-slips">
					{slips.map((s) => <li class="ddr-slip">{s}</li>)}
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="ddr-inner">
				<span class="ddr-legend ddr-legend-inner">
					<span class="ddr-ring-num ddr-ring-num-inner">inner ring</span>
					<code class="ddr-file">requireOrgUser()</code>
				</span>

				<p class="ddr-role ddr-role-inner">
					Re-checks against the DB, <strong class="ddr-auth">throws</strong> on no session /
					no active org → caught by <code class="ddr-inline">error.tsx</code>.
					<strong class="ddr-yes">This is where authorization happens.</strong>
				</p>

				<div class="ddr-page">protected page body</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Figure>

<style define:vars={{ GREEN, AMBER, sans, mono }}>
	.ddr {
		box-sizing: border-box;
		max-width: 560px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 16px 4px 6px;
		font-family: var(--sans);
		color: var(--sl-color-white);
	}

	.ddr :global(*) {
		margin: 0;
		box-sizing: border-box;
	}

	/* ── the outer ring: proxy.ts ── */
	.ddr-outer {
		position: relative;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 12px;
		padding: 26px 16px 16px;
		border: 2px dashed var(--AMBER);
		border-radius: 18px;
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--AMBER) 7%, transparent);
	}

	/* ── the inner ring: requireOrgUser() ── */
	.ddr-inner {
		position: relative;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 11px;
		padding: 26px 14px 14px;
		border: 2px solid var(--GREEN);
		border-radius: 14px;
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--GREEN) 9%, var(--sl-color-bg-sidebar));
	}

	/* ── "fieldset legend" pills straddling each box's top border ── */
	.ddr-legend {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		width: fit-content;
		padding: 3px 11px;
		border-radius: 999px;
		background: var(--sl-color-bg-sidebar);
		line-height: 1.3;
	}
	.ddr-legend-outer {
		margin-top: -39px;
		margin-left: 2px;
		border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--AMBER) 65%, transparent);
	}
	.ddr-legend-inner {
		margin-top: -39px;
		margin-left: 2px;
		border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--GREEN) 65%, transparent);
	}

	.ddr-ring-num {
		font-size: 9.5px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		padding: 1.5px 6px;
		border-radius: 999px;
		line-height: 1.4;
	}
	.ddr-ring-num-outer {
		color: #fff;
		background: var(--AMBER);
	}
	.ddr-ring-num-inner {
		color: #fff;
		background: var(--GREEN);
	}

	.ddr-file {
		font-family: var(--mono);
		font-size: 12.5px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--sl-color-white);
		background: transparent;
		padding: 0;
		white-space: nowrap;
	}

	.ddr-inline {
		font-family: var(--mono);
		font-size: 11.5px;
		background: transparent;
		padding: 0;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #c0c7d1);
		white-space: nowrap;
	}

	.ddr-role {
		font-size: 12.5px;
		line-height: 1.45;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #c0c7d1);
	}
	.ddr-role-outer .ddr-not {
		display: block;
		margin-top: 3px;
		font-weight: 800;
		color: var(--AMBER);
	}
	.ddr-role-inner .ddr-auth {
		font-weight: 800;
		color: var(--GREEN);
	}
	.ddr-role-inner .ddr-yes {
		display: block;
		margin-top: 3px;
		font-weight: 800;
		color: var(--GREEN);
	}

	/* ── the gap between the rings: what the outer ring waves through ── */
	.ddr-gap {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 6px;
		padding: 10px 12px;
		border-radius: 10px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #353c4a);
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-gray-6, #1a1f29) 45%, transparent);
	}
	.ddr-gap-head {
		font-size: 10.5px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 0.03em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #9aa3b1);
	}
	.ddr-slips {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 4px;
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
	}
	.ddr-slip {
		position: relative;
		padding-left: 16px;
		font-size: 12px;
		line-height: 1.4;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #c0c7d1);
	}
	.ddr-slip::before {
		content: '✕';
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		top: 0;
		font-size: 10px;
		font-weight: 800;
		color: var(--AMBER);
	}

	/* ── the innermost target: the page itself ── */
	.ddr-page {
		align-self: center;
		margin-top: 2px;
		padding: 7px 16px;
		border-radius: 8px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-4, #4d5666);
		background: var(--sl-color-bg-sidebar);
		font-size: 11.5px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.02em;
		color: var(--sl-color-white);
	}
</style>
